Title : Smith Island (British Columbia)
Text : '''Smith Island''' is an [[island]] off of and north of the mouth of the [[Skeena River]] in the [[British Columbia Coast|North Coast region]] of [[British Columbia]], [[Canada]].<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/37346.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Smith Island"]</ref>  It is located just south of the City of [[Prince Rupert, British Columbia|Prince Rupert]].  On its southern tip is the former settlement of [[Oceanic, British Columbia|Oceanic]].<!--a cannery in its day, I think, with that as the packing company name--><ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/52468.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Oceanic (settlement)"]</ref> '''Tsum Tsadai Inlet''' is a narrow [[inlet]] on the north side of the island, with its opening to the west.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/35334.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Tsum Tsadai Inlet"]; </ref>  '''Tsum Tsadai Rock''' is located at the inlet's opening to the sea.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/35333.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Tsum Tsadai Rock"]</ref>  [[Dashken Indian Reserve No. 22]] is on the east side of Smith Island, facing [[De Horsey Island]] which is to the east.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/64721.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Dashken 22 (Indian reserve)"]</ref>

[[Marcus Passage]] is the name of the waters to the south of the island.  To the north is [[Inverness Passage]], separating Smith Island from the [[Tsimpsean Peninsula]] and named for one of the earliest [[cannery]] companies in the area which was located at the mouth of the Skeena.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/36334.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Inverness Passage"]</ref>  The eastern end of Inverness Passage, to the north of [[De Horsey Island]], which is immediately southeast of Smith Island, and is the opening into it from the mouth of the Skeena, is [[Eleanor Passage]].<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/36582.html BC Names/GeoBC "Eleanor Passage"]</ref>  [[De Horsey Passage]] separates De Horsey Island from Smith Island on the latter's east side.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/37168.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "De Horsey Passage"]</ref>  [[Croasdaile Island]] is to the south of the southern tip of Smith Island.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/37121.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Croasdaile Island"]</ref>

